news.title: Demolish illegal buildings on Musi nalas: NGT committee
news.para: The committee, following its inspection wherein it found several buildings to be unauthorised, also recommended action against officials who permitted such constructions.

news.title: Increase property tax collection: Nashik municipal commissioner
news.para: Jadhav also directed the officials to conduct surveys and bring the properties that are without building and construction certificate (BCC) under the tax net.

news.title: Nagpur civic body begins process to auction properties of 600 tax defaulters
news.para: NMC deputy commissioner Milind Meshram told TOI that public notice warning auction of 12 properties owing arrears of over Rs5 lakh has been issued on November 21.

news.title: Plot owners seek timeline from YEIDA for handover
news.para: “Majority of the allottees have paid 60-70% of their dues while some have paid the entire amount. We were promised delivery of the plots within three years, but more than six years have passed,” said association president Tejveer Rana.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP seals building for norms violation in DLF-2
news.para: Acting on a complaint from a local resident, the enforcement team of DTCP visited the site and found unauthorised construction, zoning violations in stilt areas and filling of cutouts in contravention to the OC norms, officials told TOI.

news.title: Raymond set to rejig businesses, put professional boards in place
news.para: The group had literally started its real estate business during the pandemic constructing its first project at its Thane land parcel, earlier a mill land.

news.title: ED conducts searches against IREO group in money laundering case
news.para: ​The raids were conducted at the premises linked to the CEO and CFO of the group under the provisions of the anti-money laundering law.

news.title: DLF Cyber City Developers raises Rs 1,000 crore through NCDs
news.para: The proceeds will be utilised to refinance its existing debt resulting in interest savings and marks DCCDL's foray into the listed debt capital market and widening its investor base, the company said in a media release.

news.title: Ascendas India buys Aurum Ventures' Navi Mumbai commercial tower for Rs 353 crore
news.para: The definitive agreements between both the entities have now been executed to acquire all of the issued share capital in Building Q1 for a gross consideration of around Rs 353 crore or Singapore $64.1 million.

news.title: Decide Jaypee Infrastructure resolution plan in two months: SC to NCLT
news.para: As more than 20,000 homebuyers have been waiting for years to get possession of their flats in housing projects of JIL, they pleaded a bench of Justices A M Khanwilkar and C T Ravikumar that the process be expedited to pave the way for the new company to start construction of unfinished project.

news.title: South Korea expects revenue from real estate tax to be three times higher in 2021
news.para: The government revised the law last year, increasing the holding tax rate for homeowners, as part of efforts to cool the country's red-hot real estate market. The changes took effect this year.

news.title: EFC leases 60,000 sq ft space in Hyderabad, 38,000 sq ft in Mumbai
news.para: Average rent in Hyderabad spaces will be Rs 5,500 per seat per month while in BKC it will be Rs 14,000 per seat per month.

news.title: Lifestyle International chairman buys residential plot in Bengaluru for Rs 15.2 crore
news.para: The property jointly owned by Lumba and his wife was purchased earlier by Madhuri Genomal, wife of Sunder Genomal- MD of Page Industries and her daughter, Pamela Kripalani.

news.title: Delhi government lifts ban on construction and demolition activities
news.para: Delhi's Air Quality Index (AQI) dropped to 303 on a scale of 500, down from 499 nearly a week ago, when a thick haze hung over the city of more than 200 million people. The current AQI levels still indicate "very poor" conditions, according to government monitoring agencies.

news.title: Over 18 crore revenue records digitised in Haryana
news.para: At the state-level and in all districts, 18.5 crore records have been scanned and digitized, which will be easily available at the click of a mouse.
